## Key Relationships

| Relationship | Cardinality | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `ca_firms` → `users` | One-to-Many | A CA firm has multiple users (reviewers, firm admins) |
| `ca_firms` → `business_profiles` | One-to-Many | A CA firm manages many MSME client profiles |
| `users` → `business_profiles` | One-to-Many | An MSME owner can own multiple business profiles |
| `sources` → `documents` | One-to-Many | Each regulatory source produces many fetched documents |
| `sources` → `scraper_runs` | One-to-Many | Each source has historical scraper execution records |
| `documents` → `compliance_items` | One-to-One | Each approved document creates exactly one compliance item |
| `compliance_items` → `alerts` | One-to-Many | One regulation generates alerts for many matching businesses |
| `business_profiles` → `alerts` | One-to-Many | Each business can receive many regulatory alerts |
| `alerts` → `delivery_logs` | One-to-Many | Each alert is delivered via multiple channels (Email, WhatsApp, SMS) |

## Unique Constraints

- `alerts` has a `UNIQUE(compliance_item_id, business_profile_id)` — prevents duplicate alerts for the same regulation + business pair
- `sources.name` and `sources.short_code` are both unique
- `compliance_items.compliance_id` is unique (e.g., `"GST-001"`)
- `users.email` is unique
